pageContext.claim: “They [the EU] don't take our product. They don't take our farmers, beautiful goods. They don't take our cars. And if they do, the rate of tax is many times what we would charge them. We only charge them 2.5 percent. Their tariff is very substantially higher.”
pageContext.analysis: The EU and the U.S. have the largest bilateral trade relationship in the world, and both sides impose tariffs and other barriers on different products.
